{"id":77277,"title":"Story: an intimate human resource.","abstract":"The significance of story in providing therapeutic, person-centered care and the centrality of relationship in obtaining stories are explored in this issue of Creative Nursing. Authors explain narrative medicine, narrative nursing, and the narrative reflective process as used in education, a research cluster, and a program to help nurses thrive amid stress. Nurses tell their own and others' stories of courage, compassion for the dying, immersion in another culture, and grieving adverse life events.","date":"2014-09-25","categories":"Occupational Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25252374","annotations":[{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.810495,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Education","weight":0.767518,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Education"},{"name":"Culture","weight":0.749662,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Culture"},{"name":"Nursing","weight":0.735174,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nursing"},{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.708098,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine"},{"name":"Nurse","weight":0.658668,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nurse"},{"name":"Stress (biology)","weight":0.647429,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stress_(biology)"},{"name":"Research","weight":0.600225,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research"},{"name":"Compassion","weight":0.582719,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compassion"},{"name":"Human","weight":0.486164,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human"},{"name":"Human resources","weight":0.468416,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_resources"},{"name":"Introspection","weight":0.129065,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Introspection"},{"name":"Grief","weight":0.107046,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wik